# Mosquitto ACL — Topic-level access control
# Referenced by mosquitto.conf when authentication is enabled.
# Enforce least-privilege: each client can only touch the topics it needs.
#
# Syntax:
#   user <username>
#   topic read  <pattern>    → subscribe only
#   topic write <pattern>    → publish only
#   topic readwrite <pattern>

# ── CassiTrack backend (Spring Boot) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Subscribes to all bus positions; never publishes on the bus topics.
user cassitrack-backend
topic read cassitrack/#
# Docker healthcheck (docker-compose.yml) publishes "ping" to this topic to
# verify the broker is alive — needs write access or the container is stuck
# permanently "unhealthy", which blocks cassitrack from starting (depends_on
# mosquitto: condition: service_healthy).
topic write health

# ── Bus publisher (simulator OR real ESP32) ────────────────────────────────────
# Can only publish to its own vehicle topic — cannot subscribe or spoof other buses.
# Use one shared publisher user for the simulator.
# For real ESP32 deployments, consider one user per physical bus for stronger isolation.
user cassitrack-bus
topic write cassitrack/+/position
topic write cassitrack/+/ble
